snippet.textDisplay:
If intel can throw about 2k execution units into a videocard with 1GB of ultra high speed eDRAM and >8GB of video ram. I could see them competing with nvidia and intel. 
You can game at 720p, albeit poorly, on an intel HD 630, with only 24 EU, and that's using shared system ram.
You use high speed dedicated GDDR5(5X),GDDR6, with enough EUs, they can compete with nvidia for sure... in terms of performance. Now if they can do it for a competitive price, i don't know. But i'm excited to see what they come up with.
